Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "duguje" in different forms and positions:

1. On *duguje* meni novac. (He owes me money.)
2. *Duguješ* mi objašnjenje zašto si to uradio. (You owe me an explanation for why you did that.)
3. Kompanija *duguje* veliki dug bankama. (The company owes a large debt to the banks.)
4. Oni *duguju* zahvalnost svojim roditeljima za podršku. (They owe gratitude to their parents for their support.)
5. Ona *duguje* svoj uspeh napornom radu. (She owes her success to hard work.)
6. Kada ćeš mi *dugovati* novac? (When will you owe me money?)
7. Oni su *dugovali* porez državi. (They owed taxes to the state.)
8. Ja sam mu *dugovao* uslugu, ali sam je zaboravio. (I owed him a favor, but I forgot about it.)
9. Ona *duguje* novac banci za kredit. (She owes money to the bank for the loan.)
10. Kompanija *duguje* zahvalnost svojim zaposlenima za njihov trud. (The company owes gratitude to its employees for their hard work.)

I hope these examples help!